# age public-key recipients for HC-Map backups (M10.6, ADR-051 §D).
#
# Each non-empty, non-comment line is one recipient public key. The backup
# pipeline pipes through `age --recipients-file age-recipients.txt`, so all
# listed recipients can decrypt — listing two keys lets a 2-person split
# (operator + escrow) decrypt independently.
#
# Generate a key pair on a TRUSTED machine (NOT inside the container):
#
#   age-keygen -o hc-map.age.key
#   # → "Public key: age1qxyz..."
#
# Copy the public-key line into this file (rename to age-recipients.txt
# and place at docker/secrets/age-recipients.txt). Store the private key
# (hc-map.age.key) in your password manager. Do NOT mount the private key
# into the backup container — it is only needed for restore.
#
# CRITICAL: losing every private key listed here = unrecoverable backups.
# At least one off-host copy of each key is mandatory.

# age1example0public0key0replace0me0in0docker0secrets0age0recipients0txt
